Program.Title: Engineering Support Technician-CA (Eff: FA25)
Program.Description: The Certificate of Achievement, Engineering Support Technician offers a series of courses including foundational knowledge needed for an entry level engineering support technician. The program includes a built-in internship which allows the student to obtain hands-on experience in process manufacturing industries. Students will also be prepared to take an industry recognized certification exam.

Subrequirements.DisplayText: Complete BCIS-85, CSCI-4, CSCI-19, DFT-16, ITEC-55, PHYS-21 or PHYS-41 Complete 6 units of ENGR-99 Complete one: MATH-20, MATH-28, MATH-28S, MATH-30, MATH-30S
